				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">i3ullseye,
<br />

<br />

<br />
To start with I want to say that I&#8217;m sorely disappointed in the message you sent to Mythic.  You know what the Sorcerer community wants; yet you ignored us and squandered a golden opportunity to have our opinions heard so that you could peruse your own agenda.  I know that it is not required of you, but it would have been extremely nice if you had consulted us before hand.
<br />

<br />
What the Sorcerer Community really wants:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Crowd Control</span>
<br />

<br />
We need to be able to effectively crowd control in a large group situations (so that means high red, low purple, and the occasional purple).  We need to be able to do this reliably, not the Mez and pray routine we currently have to endure.  If we can&#8217;t crowd control reliably, groups will not trust us to crowd control at all. Before anyone thinks any of these suggestions are overpowered, kindly refer to the Midguard Healer&#8217;s spell list!
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Crowd Control Suggestions</span><UL TYPE=SQUARE><LI>Reduced Mez resistance.
<br />
<LI>Remove the variable duration nonsense, interrupts, diminishing returns and resists are enough to contend with.
<br />
<LI>Faster casting on Mez spells across the board.  That Mez does me no good if by the time I cast it the Mob is already beating on the cleric.
<br />
<LI>Increased Mez range.
<br />
<LI>Instant cast Mez spells on timers for emergencies.
<br />
<LI>Point Blank AE Stuns (that do NOT break Mez).
<br />
</UL>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Group Desirability</span>
<br />

<br />
We need to be able to bring something to a group even in situations where crowd control in not required.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Group Desirability Suggestions</span><UL TYPE=SQUARE><LI>Concentration based Endurance Regeneration bufs.
<br />
<LI>Concentration based Power Regeneration bufs.
<br />
<LI>Concentration based Agro multiplier bufs.
<br />
<LI>Concentration based Agro reduction bufs.
<br />
</UL>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Realm Vs Realm</span>
<br />

<br />
Currently in RvR the Sorcerer is merely a good source of RP&#8217;s for the opposing realms.  That&#8217;s about all we are good for, this needs to change.  
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Realm Vs Realm Suggestions</span><UL TYPE=SQUARE><LI>Realm points for Mez and Debufs.
<br />
<LI>Invisibility and Detect Stealth spells.
<br />
<LI>Make our spells work in RvR (Amnesia, Confusion, and maybe even a limited form of Charm).
<br />
<LI>Illusions.  I would love to be able to masquerade as one of the enemy, or baring that I&#8217;d settle for being to be able to disguise the fact that I&#8217;m a sitting duck (Illusion Armsmen).</UL>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Misc Suggestions</span><UL TYPE=SQUARE><LI>Out of combat pet healing.
<br />
<LI>Increased survivability, Unlike other casters we are forced to cast on mobs that are not already good and pissed at other group members, thus we take a considerable beating.  We need something to alleviate this problem.
<br />
</UL>
<br />

<br />
Lastly,
<br />

<br />
      <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">First the run spell needs to work on the pet. This has been broken for far too long. Maybe making it a single target spell with a 10 minute duration would better for this. It would also allow it to get away from being a song, which is totally out of place.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You constantly make suggestions that would <span style="font-weight: bold">hurt</span> our class more then they would help it.  I do <span style="font-weight: bold">not</span> want to be casting a single target run buf on every person in my group every 10 minutes only to have it expire right when I need it most.  The fact that the run buf icon blinks does not make it a song.  Why are you so hung up on this issue? No other Sorcerer that I know of even cares.
<br />

<br />
I take no credit for these ideas, most came from this and various other message boards.  
<br />

<br />
Syth,
<br />
32nd Level Malefice,
<br />
Pellinor</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
