				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">And more specifically……
<br />

<br />
Your Questions and accusations:
<br />

<br />
   <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>
<br />
Crowd Control 
<br />
We need to be able to effectively crowd control in a large group situations (so that means high red, low purple, and the occasional purple). We need to be able to do this reliably, not the Mez and pray routine we currently have to endure. If we can’t crowd control reliably, groups will not trust us to crowd control at all. Before anyone thinks any of these suggestions are overpowered, kindly refer to the Midguard Healer’s spell list!
<br />
<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>
<br />

<br />
  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>
<br />
Group Desirability 
<br />
We need to be able to bring something to a group even in situations where crowd control in not required.
<br />
<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>
<br />

<br />
   <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>
<br />
Realm Vs Realm 
<br />
Currently in RvR the Sorcerer is merely a good source of RP’s for the opposing realms. That’s about all we are good for, this needs to change. 
<br />
<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>
<br />

<br />
All that. Now read my very last comments:
<br />

<br />
   <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>
<br />
The general community if furious at this point. The frustration level is high. Sorcerors were fairly rare to begin with, not that many groups can not rely on their Mez to be quite as effective in groups, they are getting less group invites. Not only have we always been weak in PvP (relatively) we now may have less Sorcerors actually making it to high enough level to even consider PvP. Many choose the sorcerer with the idea that we will be the best in crowd control and that is our niche. As sweeping changes are made to class abilities as a whole, it is becoming apparent that we are NOT necessarily the best at Crowd Control, and these changes actually do not address the initial imbalances they were intended for, but only weaken the other classes grouped into the category affected by the change. 
<br />
If by beefing up the matter line you could add more group and PvP functionality, it could go a long way toward bringing the sorcerer back up to the standards everyone has come to expect from the class.
<br />
  <HR></BLOCKQUOTE>
<br />

<br />
Now what the hell were you reading? Basically I think I should thank you for lengthening out the statements I made in my closing paragraph for me. 
<br />

<br />
And as far as the speed song (it pulses and actually lists as a song, not a spell) I am suggesting they try to make it a single target item so it may overcome its brokenness. I think that our pet starting as an enemy is part of the coding problem with it, and making it castable ON a target could overcome this. This would also allow us to buff someone not in our group, and for others to NOT have to stay within spell range of us.
<br />

<br />
I have detailed these suggestions out time and again on the Pendragon boards, and this report is meant for there. So the ideas and the underlying information is generally known and acknowledged. I am sorry if I did not break that down completely, but that report was written for the Pendragon forums, not for here. I only posted it here out of courtesy.
<br />

<br />
And that wasn’t even the question asked. I merely put that in there to keep reminding them that the spell is broken. 
<br />

<br />
Man, tough room here…. I heartily recommend reading all future posts like this twice before flying into a fit of rage!
<br />

