			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">i3ullseye,
<br />
      <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>So I ask the question to all of you then. 
<br />
Which one of our spell lines would be seen as incomplete or lacking? 
<br />
Now after reading that you tell me if my report is very far off the mark.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>
<br />

<br />
The portion of your report that indicates the Matter line of spells is incomplete is dead on the money, Matter is indeed underpowered (but not as much as everyone seems to think).  Every point in Matter spec increases the AF provided by our shield spells by 3 (at level 30), and I&#8217;m told that this added AF gets better with the higher versions of the shield spell.  Furthermore, the Matter spec DoT is an enemy caster&#8217;s (or archer&#8217;s) nightmare.  The DoT takes them completely out of the battle for its duration.  Regardless, you are correct the Matter line is incomplete.
<br />

<br />
Now, the rest of your report is what I consider &#8220;far off the mark&#8221;.  You made several suggestions that no one wants, while neglecting to mention the suggestions we have asked for.  Run song is fine, we do not want it as a single target buf.  Levitation is cute, but hardly going to solve our class problems.  A force based pushback spell, no idea how this would be implemented, you&#8217;ll need to clarify.  Your damage reflection shield is a flight of fancy, while the damage reduction would be nice, it would most likely end up being implemented as a totally useless self-only damage shield.
<br />

<br />
      <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> The general community if furious at this point. The frustration level is high. Sorcerors were fairly rare to begin with, not that many groups can not rely on their Mez to be quite as effective in groups, they are getting less group invites. Not only have we always been weak in PvP (relatively) we now may have less Sorcerors actually making it to high enough level to even consider PvP. Many choose the sorcerer with the idea that we will be the best in crowd control and that is our niche. As sweeping changes are made to class abilities as a whole, it is becoming apparent that we are NOT necessarily the best at Crowd Control, and these changes actually do not address the initial imbalances they were intended for, but only weaken the other classes grouped into the category affected by the change. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Whole heartedly agree, this was a good paragraph.
<br />

<br />
      <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Man, tough room here&#8230;. I heartily recommend reading all future posts like this twice before flying into a fit of rage! </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I read your post twice, and I did not fly into a fit of rage.  I merely tried to give constructive criticism in as polite a fashion as I could manage in my agitated state.  Trust me, when I fly into a fit of rage you&#8217;ll know about it.
<br />

<br />
You need to stop treating every contradicting view as a personal attack.  I have no quarrels with you, I merely disagree with how your handling some portions of your job as a class TL.  If my comments are annoying you then let me know.  I&#8217;ll stop wasting my time trying to help you better the class we all enjoy playing.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Edit: The class we use to all enjoy playing.</span>
<br />

<br />
Syth,
<br />
33rd Level Malefice,
<br />
Pellinor</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
